article.headline: Chenery's 23 lead Binghamton past Army 75-68
article.description: — Tymu Chenery had 23 points in Binghamton's 75-68 victory against Army on Saturday.
article.story: BINGHAMTON, N.Y. -- — Tymu Chenery had 23 points in Binghamton's 75-68 victory against Army on Saturday. Chenery was 6-of -15 shooting, including 0 for 5 from 3-point range, and went 11 for 14 from the line for the Bearcats (4-3). Symir Torrence added 20 points, eight rebounds and six assists. Nehemiah Benson had 10 points. Ryan Curry led the way for the Black Knights (0-6) with 13 points. Josh Scovens added 12 points for Army. Charlie Peterson also put up 11 points and 10 rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
